text.tspan: Income as a human need satisfier

flowRoot.flowPara: International MER and PPP income more than doubled between 1971 and 2014. Despite this growth, MER income accounts for less than one third, and PPP income for less than half, of historical improvements in life expectancy.

text.tspan: Nutrition as a human need satisfier
Energy services as human need satisfiers

flowRoot.flowPara: International food supply increased by only 18% between 1971 and 2014. Despite this modest increase, it can account for close to half the improvement in life expectancy.
International residential electricity per capita usage almost tripled between 1971 and 2014, and can account for 60% of improvements in life expectancy.
